</p>
<a name="Tips" id="Tips"></a><h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=LXC&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Tips">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline"> Tips </span></h2>
<ul><li> Warning: killing lxc-related processes from host may cause htop to segfault. There is no known workaround for it. <code>kill(1)</code> works just fine.
</li><li> Do not use kill -9 to switch off virtual machine. Use <code>lxc-stop -n vm<i>n</i></code>.
</li><li> REAL DANGER: DO NOT EVEN TRY TO USE /proc/sysrq-trigger INSIDE CONTAINER, IT WILL AFFECT HOST SYSTEM! This is security flaw that will have to be investigated.
</li></ul>
